squatter
Homonym Number: 1
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a person occupying land to which he has no legal right and to which he does not pay rental: N.I. Maori land: S.I. also land `belonging to' the Company a. referring specifically to those (esp. Company immigrants) living temporarily on any land they could get a foothold on while waiting for sections to be surveyed and/or granted to them; including most of those who arrived in Wellington by the first ships, as the NZ Company had not yet bought or surveyed land enough
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:cf. Morris: English use 1835
